The paper discusses machine learning algorithms and their application to real-world problems, which suggests that it could belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The specific focus on class imbalance and concept drift also suggests that it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The mention of data streams and the need for learners to be adaptive suggests a possible connection to cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval), which often deal with streaming data and changing distributions.
